<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-30 11:49 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5116 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-SUPER-BOWL-NYT &LR;      01-30 0460
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-SUPER-BOWL-NYT </SLUG>
  
 MIAMI: know that.''  
<TEXT>
<P>
   So, how will the running games be defended?
</P>
<P>
   ``Miami, the first time they played Denver, held Terrell to 29
rushing yards,'' Blackmon said. ``They stunted a lot on defense and
based those stunts on Denver tendencies. They created disruption
with run blitzes into the Denver offensive line. They held them
down and won the game.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the rematch, Miami came back and tried the same thing. But
Denver changed everything around. Miami was blitzing and stunting
to the wrong holes. And when you do that, play the guessing game
and guess wrong against that line and Terrell, you are hurting your
team. We won't live on that. It's too risky.''
</P>
<P>
   Atlanta wants to play gap control, center its defense on the
idea that each player must stand tall in his area of responsibility
and not float. In essence, the Falcons' defense is based on an
imaginative triangle scheme. The three players who form the
triangle are tackles Travis Hall and Shane Dronett and middle
linebacker Jessie Tuggle.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody in the NFL holds _ they do it a little better than
most,'' Rich Brooks, Atlanta's defensive coordinator, said of the
Denver offensive line. ``So, we have talked a lot about not only
maintaining gaps but also shedding blocks. Our defense is
predicated on the two tackles, Travis Hall and Shane Dronett, and
the middle linebacker, Jessie Tuggle. We work from the middle to
the outside toward both ends. All defense begins with defending the
middle. It's going to be very interesting what happens in the long
running game. We have allowed only three runs all season of 20
yards or more; they have 17 of those. Who's going to win that
battle?''
</P>
<P>
   Three important Denver defenders against the run are left tackle
Keith Traylor and linebackers Bill Romanowski and John Mobley.
</P>
<P>
   ``Traylor can make the big hit,'' said Greg Robinson, Denver's
defensive coordinator. ``Romanowski is a hitter in the run and pass
game. Mobley moves sideline to sideline and makes effort plays. We
need all 11 in the run game, but these guys have the ability to
really get us going.''
</P>
<P>
   The running game is a product of discipline and desire.
Execution. Commitment. One team will most likely win this Super
Bowl by rushing. The other will finish all wet.
</P>
<P>
   ``I take it personally upon myself to lead in our defense
against Terrell Davis,'' Tuggle said. ``I did not come this far to
lose.''
</P>
<P>
   The Broncos' Crockett countered: ``The desire on our team is
crazy. We have a chance to put ourselves in history as one of the
greatest teams ever. We can become the sixth team in Super Bowl
history to win back-to-back championships. That's something special
to shoot for. We're going to take our best run at that.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
