<SLUG> BC-IRS-VISIT31-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    IRS wheels into towns to help residents file income taxes
 &HT;    By Gene Tharpe
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If you live more than 40 miles from the nearest
Internal Revenue Service, the IRS may be coming for a neighborly
visit to help you file your 1998 income taxes.
</P>
<P>
   Don't panic. They're not coming to your house but, beginning
Monday, the IRS will send vans with tax workers to 24 cities in
Georgia that are more than 40 miles from the nearest IRS office.
</P>
<P>
   Monday, the vans will visit the first three of the cities:
Elberton, LaGrange and Tifton.
</P>
<P>
   Tax workers on the WOW (``We're on Wheels'') vans will help
people prepare 1040EZ, 1040A and simple 1040 forms with itemized
deductions. They will also answer questions and provide forms to
taxpayers who want to prepare their own returns.
</P>
<P>
   ``This service is unique to Georgia,'' said Eric Roberts,
spokesman for the IRS district office in Atlanta. The vans will be
staffed by IRS workers each day, from about 2 to 8 p.m. The hours
will vary some from site to site, but you may call 404-388-7691 for
each site's time.
</P>
<P>
   The van service is one of several steps the IRS is taking around
the nation to fulfill the congressional mandate of the IRS
Restructuring and Reform Act of 1998 that directed the IRS to
improve its service to taxpayers.
</P>
<P>
   The dates, the cities and the addresses where the vans will be
located are:
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 1: Elberton, Holiday Inn Express, 970 Elbert St.; LaGrange,
West Georgia Technical School; and Tifton, Tifton Mall.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 2: Bainbridge, Bainbridge Mall; Carrollton, Pilot
Auditorium, 118 S. White St.; and Toccoa, Courthouse Annex, Tugalo
Rd.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 3: Blairsville, Union County Bank, 59 Hwy. 515; and
Moultrie, Moultrie Tech Seminar Center, 361 Industrial Dr.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 4: Blakely, Maddox Memorial Library, 628 Columbia Rd.;
Ellijay, Gilmer County Bank, 1 Westside Square; and Thomaston,
Thomaston Civic Center, 101 Civic Center Dr.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 5: Americus, Georgia Southwestern College, 800 Wheatley
St.; Dahlonega, Lumpkin County Courthouse, 99 Courthouse Hill; and
Griffin, Senior Citizens Center, 1005 Memorial Dr.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 8: Washington, Pope Center, Lexington Avenue; and Waycross,
Okefenokee Heritage Center, 1460 N. Augusta Rd.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 9: Douglas, Satilla Regional Library, 201 Coffee Ave.; and
Waynesboro, Burke County Library, 412 4th St.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 10: Sparta, Youth Opportunity Center, Augusta Highway; and
Vidalia, Council Chambers, 114 Jackson St.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 11: Dublin, Emory Thomas Auditorium, Riverview Park Drive;
and Sandersville, Rosa M. Turbuton Library, 314 S. Harris St.
</P>
<P>
   Feb. 12: Milledgeville, Baldwin County Library, 151 S. Jefferson
St.; and Statesboro, County Annex, 115 N. Main St.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
