<SLUG> BC-NY-SCHOOL-ILLNESS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EXPERTS SEEKING CAUSE OF ILLNESS AT BRONX SCHOOL
</HEADLINE>
   (dal) 
 By SUSAN SACHS    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Environmental testing continued Saturday at a Bronx
school that was evacuated twice last week after students and
teachers became ill there.
</P>
<P>
   A number of students who had been on the second floor at
Intermediate School 135, at 2441 Wallace Ave. in Bronxdale, began
to suffer from severe nausea, headaches or chest pains on Thursday
and again on Friday. Several were taken to hospitals for tests.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators are checking the water in the school's drinking
fountains, as well as its furnace and indoor air quality. Because
some people reported the odor of rotten eggs, which is often
related to sulfur dioxide, the officials also planned to check the
oil in the school's heating system for that chemical during tests
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   While the cause of the illnesses at I.S. 135 has not been
pinpointed, school officials said they had made progress in the
investigation of a separate spate of illnesses at another Bronx
school.
</P>
<P>
   Chiara Coletti, director of communications for the Board of
Education, said that noxious gases coming from the Bathgate
Industrial Park were responsible for the nausea and dizziness that
overcame teachers and students at Public School 4 in the Bathgate
section of the Bronx last Monday and Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   City and state environmental agencies will attempt this week to
pinpoint where in the industrial park the gases are originating,
she added.
</P>
<P>
   Students at a third Bronx school, Public School 19, also were
sickened last week, by what was described as an alcohol-like smell.
Ms. Coletti said officials are looking at the possibility that
alcohol or some other substance may have spilled in the nurse's
office and its odor spread through the ventilation system.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-30-99 1436EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990130.0155 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-30 14:38 </DATE_TIME>
