<HEADLINE>
BRONX MAN IS ARRESTED IN A SERIES OF RAPES OF MASSEUSES 
 (DW)
</HEADLINE>
   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A Bronx man was arrested and was facing charges of
rape and robbery Saturday in a series of attacks on masseuses in
Manhattan, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   The man, identified as Darryl Bolden, 35, was picked up after
phone records revealed that he had made phone calls to the victims,
said a police official who spoke on the condition of anonymity.
</P>
<P>
   The police said that Bolden, who is 6 feet 10 inches tall and
weighs about 340 pounds, matched the description given by the
victims.
</P>
<P>
   He was last arrested for two assaults in the early 1980s, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
   The police began looking for a serial rapist after Jan. 15, when
a 50-year-old masseuse living on West 69th Street reported that a
man who came in for an appointment had raped her and stolen $100.
</P>
<P>
   A 33-year-old masseuse in the same building then told the police
that she had been robbed of $400 on Dec. 13 by a client who fit the
same description. A few days later, a 46-year-old woman reported
that she had been raped and robbed by a man who fit the same
description in her home near West 75th Street on Sept. 24. Another
woman reported a similar attack on Jan. 21 near East 60th Street.
</P>
</TEXT>
