<P>
   OLY-CONFLICT-OFINTEREST _ Alex Gilady is a part-time executive
for NBC. He also is an IOC member who works on the committee's
radio/TV commission. He was a middleman in the negotiations between
the two entities for the TV contract _ and made money from both
sides. He is an example of people who work both sides of the fence
behind the Olympic scenes and raises conflict-of-interest
questions. This system apparently will continue even while the IOC
cleans up its act on awarding bid cities. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50. MOVED
</P>
