   GOLF
</P>
<P>
   GLF-DUVAL _ David Duval is in one of the hottest ``zones'' in
golf history, a stretch that continued last Sunday with a
record-setting 59 at the Bob Hope. His golf game is so solid, so
terrifying for competitors, that they all wish he'd pack it up and
go home. ``We're playing for second,'' is the common refrain. For
years, critics snickered that Duval didn't have what it takes to
win. Now, after winning the first two tournaments of 1999 and more
than an $1 million in January, they think he may never lose.
(Sheeley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40. MOVED
</P>
